OL,3,CAlmost one in 10 believe they may have
OL,4,Clong Covid, research finds
OL,6,FAlmost one in 10 people in England
OL,7,Fthink they could have long Covid,
OL,8,Faccording to analysis of national data.
OL,10,FResearchers at the University of
OL,11,FSouthampton examined information
OL,12,Fcollected by NHS England which showed
OL,13,F4.8% of people reported having the
OL,14,Fcondition, with higher rates in
OL,15,Fdeprived areas and people with
OL,16,Fparticular ethnic backgrounds,
OL,17,Fparents, carers and those with another
OL,18,Flong-term condition.
