OL,3,CAlmost one in 10 believe they may have
OL,4,Clong Covid, research finds
OL,6,FThe researchers analysed more than
OL,7,F750,000 responses to the GP Patient
OL,8,FSurvey (England) 2023 and found people
OL,9,Faged under 25, males, people from
OL,10,Fparticular ethnic minorities, and
OL,11,Fpeople without long-term conditions
OL,12,Fwere more likely to be unsure if they
OL,13,Fhad long Covid.
OL,15,FThey found men were generally less
OL,16,Flikely to seek medical advice than
OL,17,Fwomen, which they say could partly
OL,18,Fexplain the higher level of
OL,19,Funcertainty with stigma and self-doubt
OL,20,Falso discouraging people from seeking
OL,21,Fa diagnosis.
