OL,3,CAlmost one in 10 believe they may have
OL,4,Clong Covid, research finds
OL,6,FMirembe Woodrow, who is studying for a
OL,7,FPhD at Southampton and who carried out
OL,8,Fthe analysis, said: "We were really
OL,9,Fsurprised to find so many people
OL,10,Fweren't sure whether they had long
OL,11,FCovid or not, and the study shows
OL,12,Fthere is still work to do to increase
OL,13,Fawareness of the condition and remove
OL,14,Fbarriers to accessing diagnosis,
OL,15,Ftreatment and support.
OL,17,F"We don't want long Covid to be
OL,18,Fanother factor that contributes to the
OL,19,Fwidening health gap in the UK."
